{"title_page": "Viva (2015 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2015 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Viva\n| image = Viva poster.png\n| caption = Theatrical release poster\n| director = [[Paddy Breathnach]]\n| producer = \n| writer = [[Mark O'Halloran]]\n| starring = [[H\u00e9ctor Medina (actor)|H\u00e9ctor Medina]]\n| music = Stephen Rennicks\n| cinematography = Cathal Watters\n| editing = Stephen O'Connell\n| studio = \n| distributor =  \n| released = {{Film date|2015|09|04|[[Telluride Film Festival|Telluride]]|2016|8|19|Ireland|df=yes}}\n| runtime = 100 minutes<!--Theatrical runtime: 100:15--><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/viva-film | title=''Viva'' (15) | work=[[British Board of Film Classification]] | date=30 August 2016 | accessdate=1 September 2016}}</ref>\n| country = Ireland\n| language = Spanish\n| budget = \n| gross = $48,995<ref>{{mojo title|id=viva}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''Viva''''' is a 2015 Spanish-language Irish [[drama film]], set in Cuba, directed by [[Paddy Breathnach]] and written by [[Mark O'Halloran]]. The film stars [[H\u00e9ctor Medina (actor)|H\u00e9ctor Medina]] as a young drag performer who, after reuniting with his estranged father, must come to terms with his sexuality.\n\nThe film was selected as the Irish entry for the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[88th Academy Awards]].<ref name=\"Ireland\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/09/oscars-ireland-selects-cuban-viva-foreign-language-film-entry-1201530051/ |title=Oscars: Ireland Selects Cuba-Set 'Viva' As Foreign Language Film Entry |work=Deadline |date=16 September 2015 |accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"scannain\">{{cite web|url=http://www.scannain.com/irish/viva-oscar-entry |title=Irish Film: Viva selected as Irish entry for Best Foreign Language Film for 88th Oscars |work=Ccannain |date=16 September 2015 |accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"HWR\">{